"title":"Inflammatory Myopathies",
"jsonContent":{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_rm_s14",
"title":{
"__html":"Inflammatory Myopathies"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"57c717",
"children":[
"Inflammatory Myopathies"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_rm_s14_1",
"title":{
"__html":"Diagnosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"e8fd5b",
"children":[
"The major inflammatory myopathies are polymyositis, dermatomyositis, and inclusion body myositis. Certain medications (glucocorticoids, statins) or alcohol may also cause a toxic myopathy."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"9158d4",
"children":[
"The characteristic finding in polymyositis and dermatomyositis is the gradual onset of painless proximal muscle, pharyngeal, and respiratory muscle weakness."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"dc5f3a",
"children":[
"Photosensitivity rashes are commonly associated with dermatomyositis. ",
{
"type":"alert",
"children":[
"The presence of Gottron papules (scaly, purplish papules and plaques over the metacarpal and interphalangeal joints) or a heliotrope rash (edematous lilac discoloration of periorbital tissue) is virtually diagnostic of dermatomyositis."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"98b329",
"children":[
"An antisynthetase syndrome is characterized by interstitial lung disease, inflammatory polyarthritis, fever, Raynaud phenomenon, mechanic's hands (scaly, rough, dry, cracked horizontal lines on the palmar and lateral aspects of the fingers), and increased risk of sudden death. It can be seen in patients with polymyositis or dermatomyositis but not with inclusion body myositis."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"a5bf00",
"children":[
"Inclusion body myositis is characterized by the insidious onset of symptoms, which involve proximal and distal muscles, frequently with an asymmetric distribution. Quadriceps, wrist, and finger flexor muscle weakness is common."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_rm_s14_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Testing"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"fa6a5a",
"children":[
"Testing"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"81fbb3",
"children":[
"Diagnostic tests for inflammatory myositis include measurement of serum ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"creatine kinase",
"children":[
"CK"
]
},
" and aldolase levels and ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"electromyography",
"children":[
"EMG"
]
},
"."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"7ba0f8",
"children":[
"Muscle biopsy is the definitive study. MRI may assess the degree of muscle inflammation and damage and may be helpful when other diagnostic studies are equivocal or to identify the most promising biopsy site."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"6c1697",
"children":[
"Autoantibodies to aminoacyl-transfer (t)RNA synthetase enzymes (e.g., anti–Jo-1 antibodies) are associated with the antisynthetase syndrome."
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"285e8b",
"children":[
"Serum ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"aspartate aminotransferase",
"children":[
"AST"
]
},
" and ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"alanine aminotransferase",
"children":[
"ALT"
]
},
" levels may be elevated in myositis, mimicking liver disease."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"e577c8",
"children":[
"Muscle pain in patients with an inflammatory myopathy is atypical and, if present, is generally mild."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_rm_s14_inline_t1"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"65edeb",
"children":[
"If myositis is unresponsive to treatment, consider a diagnosis of inclusion body myositis."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_rm_s14_3",
"title":{
"__html":"Malignancy and Inflammatory Myopathies"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"d1470d",
"children":[
"Malignancy and Inflammatory Myopathies"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"19f1b7",
"children":[
"The association between malignancy and inflammatory myositis is clear. Commonly associated cancers include ovarian, lung, pancreas, stomach, and colon cancers and lymphoma. Sex- and age-appropriate cancer screening should be performed at the time of diagnosis and at periodic intervals thereafter."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_rm_s14_4",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"6fe44a",
"children":[
"High-dose oral glucocorticoid therapy is first-line treatment for polymyositis and dermatomyositis."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"b29852",
"children":[
"Adding methotrexate and/or azathioprine may be indicated if disease is refractory to high-dose glucocorticoid therapy or as glucocorticoid-sparing agents. Inclusion body myositis usually does not respond to immunosuppression."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"2b0bfb",
"children":[
"Baseline bone mineral density testing is indicated in patients who undergo long-term high-dose glucocorticoid therapy. Begin prophylactic therapy for osteoporosis with calcium and vitamin D supplementation and bisphosphonates."
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"2",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_rm_f17"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"a92947",
"children":[
"Suspect glucocorticoid-induced myopathy in patients with continued or new-onset worsening of proximal muscle weakness despite normalization of muscle enzyme levels."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"dd5ea8",
"children":[
"Always check ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"thyroid-stimulating hormone",
"children":[
"TSH"
]
},
" levels when evaluating myopathy."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"3",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_rm_f18"
],
"forceOpen":true
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_rm_s14_5",
"title":{
"__html":"Test Yourself"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"7866cc",
"children":[
