]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"f10f37",
"class":"test",
"children":[
"A 40-year-old man has a 6-week history of dyspnea, dry cough, fever, decreased appetite, and weight loss. He has progressive difficulty climbing stairs and reaching up to shampoo his hair. He has deep fissures and thickened skin on the palms of his hands."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"e2ba7b",
"class":"test_answer",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Answer:"
]
},
" ",
"For diagnosis, choose antisynthetase syndrome."
]
}
]
}
]
